  "verdict": "Carrier-native Pati-Salam -> SO(10) proton decay (OPTIONAL gauged UV branch B; NOT the default boundary-only reading A). M_PS lands on the TFPT scalaron scale M_s=3.06e+13 GeV (x1.38-1.32), independent of the gauge running -- the TFPT-specific coincidence. GOLDEN CHANNEL p->e+pi0: (1) minimal 16-content M_GUT=2.40e+15 -> tau_p=4.19e+33 yr is EXCLUDED by Super-K (2.4e+34 yr) even at the optimistic band edge -> KILL. (2) The single E8-allowed 45 +(15,1,1) raises M_GUT to 5.80e+15 -> tau_p=1.46e+35 yr at 1-loop -> CONSISTENT and decisively probed by Hyper-Kamiokande (20 yr). (3) But at 2-loop M_GUT drops to 2.80e+15 -> tau_p=7.72e+33 yr < Super-K -> a latent TENSION (only the optimistic O(3) hadronic edge / GUT-threshold headroom saves it). So the whole PS branch is proton-safe ONLY with +(15,1,1) and ONLY marginally -- the E8 hull supplies just one 45 (v247), so this is a sharp, dated kill-test, not a knob. Second channel p->nubar K+ (DUNE/JUNO-optimised) is SUBDOMINANT in non-SUSY dim-6 gauge mediation: tau_p~4.6e+35 yr for +(15,1,1) sits above even the next-gen reach -> data_limited (R_nuK is an external nuisance, not a TFPT primitive). FIREWALL: tau_p is a downstream branch prediction, never [E]/\\veri{}; if only the minimal PS stage is gauged its leptoquarks mediate rare LFV, not p->e+pi0 (v385)."
